response.Q0: First few attempts were just to see how it went and see if I learnt anything. I ended up clicking on the furthest points and picking the largest number to aim for without clicking on too many nodes to check.
response.Q1: I realised the furthest nodes had the largest points (both + and -) and picking the largest +number to aim for without clicking on too many nodes in between to check.
response.Q2: Obviously there wasn't enough time to check all the nodes, plus each check cost points so it was just a matter of aiming for the largest points uncovered for the least nodes checked as quickly as possible.
